A_8}|, where S is the set of all injective functions (permutations of 8 digits from 9). The total number of injective functions |S| is P(9,8) = 9 * 8 * 7 *... * 2 = 362880. Now, compute |A_j|: the number of permutations where the j-th position has a digit less than j. For position j, the number of digits less than j is (j - 1). So, we need to choose a digit for position j from 1 to j - 1, and then permute the remaining 7 digits from the remaining 8 digits.
